sequenceDiagram
    participant TL as Technical Lead / Project Architect
    participant OE as Orchestration Engine
    participant KR as Knowledge Repository
    participant AAR as AI Agent Runtime
    participant TIG as Tool Integration Gateway
    participant EE as Execution Engine
    participant GM as Governance Module

    TL->>OE: Define specification scope and submit request
    OE->>OE: Workflow Engine creates specification workflow
    OE->>OE: Task Manager instantiates: Generate Spec → Review → Validate → Approve
    OE->>AAR: Assign Generate task to Documentation Agent
    AAR->>KR: Read architecture context, domain model, UL
    KR-->>AAR: Architectural views, domain model, ubiquitous language
    AAR->>TIG: Invoke AI Provider for specification drafting
    TIG-->>AAR: Draft specification content
    AAR-->>OE: Draft specification artifact

    OE->>AAR: Assign Review task to Review Agent
    AAR->>KR: Read draft + architecture + acceptance criteria standards
    KR-->>AAR: Consistency context
    AAR->>TIG: Invoke AI Provider for specification review
    TIG-->>AAR: Review findings
    AAR-->>OE: Review report (completeness, unambiguous AC, architecture alignment)

    OE->>AAR: Assign Validate task to Validation Agent
    AAR-->>OE: Validation result

    OE->>EE: Deliver specification candidate
    EE->>EE: Validation Engine: structure, AC completeness, consistency
    EE->>GM: Submit for governance

    GM->>GM: Documentation Standards Validator: specification structure compliance
    Note over GM: Specification approval is mandatory —<br/>specifications drive implementation
    GM->>TL: Route to formal Approval Gate
    TL-->>GM: Approval decision

    alt Approved
        GM->>GM: Audit Logger records formal approval
        GM->>KR: Persist approved specification to Documentation Store
        KR-->>OE: Specification available — implementation workflows may be triggered
    else Rejected
        GM->>OE: Rejection report with findings
        OE->>TL: Rejection report delivered
    end
